The paper deals with distributed algorithms in a message-passing model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus of the paper is on symmetry-breaking, which is a topic in Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Algorithmic Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses complexity measures, which is a topic in Algorithms (cs.AL) and Complexity Theory (cs.CC). The use of graphs as a representation of the communication network suggests a connection to Network Information Theory (cs.NI). Finally, the discussion of efficiency and energy consumption suggests a connection to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
